DOCUMENT SHAPE:
The artifact is a markdown document. Frontmatter carries the decision; optional `##` sections carry the body. Valid shapes:

- Commit (frontmatter `type: commit` plus `subject:`), with optional sections `## Body` (one item, concise self-contained explanation) OR the detailed trio `## Body Summary` / `## Body Details` / `## Body Footer` (one item each — never combine `Body` with the trio), plus optional `## Files` (one item per file to include) and `## Excluded Files` (one item per exclusion, text `path | reason`; valid reasons: internal_ignore, not_task_related, sensitive, deferred):

```markdown
---
type: commit
subject: fix(auth): prevent token expiry race
---

## Body Summary
- [BS-1] Prevents a race where refreshed tokens could expire mid-request.

## Body Details
- [BD-1] The expiry check now happens after refresh; covers the concurrent-refresh edge case.

## Excluded Files
- [X-1] notes/todo.md | not_task_related
```

- Skip (no commit needed):

```markdown
---
type: skip
reason: Only generated artifacts changed; nothing to commit.
---
```

